<div class="body_box_header">Custom door/plat/button sounds by Knightmare</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">Gard</a> on Sunday, August 8, 2004 - 04:02</small><br /><br />
<p>For those of you working with Quake II, Knightmare has found a neat way to add support for custom <i>door</i>, <i>plat</i> and <i>button sounds</i>. This will all be in the next release of KMQuake2, but it can easily be added to any MOD.</p> 

<p>Check out the new <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/530">Custom door/plat/button sounds</a> RUST Tutorial, and the <a href="http://forums.gamedesign.net/viewtopic.php?t=49025">Quake II Forum</a> for the related discussion.</p>
